{"metadata":{"kernelspec":{"name":"","display_name":""},"language_info":{"name":"python"},"kaggle":{"accelerator":"nvidiaTeslaT4","dataSources":[{"sourceType":"datasetVersion","sourceId":15685078,"datasetId":10045196,"databundleVersionId":16623279},{"sourceType":"datasetVersion","sourceId":15336285,"datasetId":9809498,"databundleVersionId":16244466}],"dockerImageVersionId":31329,"isInternetEnabled":true,"language":"python","sourceType":"notebook","isGpuEnabled":true}},"nbformat_minor":5,"nbformat":4,"cells":[{"id":"2f93efd9","cell_type":"markdown","source":"# SimCLR — Multi-Anatomy MRI Anomaly Detection\n\nThis notebook trains **three separate SimCLR models** for artifact detection:\n\n| # | Anatomy | Dataset | Description |\n|---|---------|---------|-------------|\n| 1 | **Knee** | FastMRI (preprocessed) | Single anatomy, single contrast |\n| 2 | **Brain** | IXI (T1 + T2) | Single anatomy, mixed contrast |\n| 3 | **Combined** | Both datasets merged | Multi-anatomy generalist model |\n\n## Key Improvements (vs brain-only v1)\n- **Temperature τ = 0.5** — prevents partial collapse with small real batch size (64 negatives)\n- **Learning rate = 1e-3** — stronger signal to escape flat loss regions\n- **Stronger augmentations** — crop scale 0.5–1.0 (was 0.8–1.0), rotation ±20° (was ±15°)\n- **Larger projection head** — 512 → 2048 → 2048 → 128 (SimCLR v2 style)\n- **25 epochs per model** — ~4.5h per model on Kaggle T4\n\n## Pipeline per Model\n1. Train SimCLR encoder (NT-Xent contrastive loss)\n2. Extract L2-normalized 512-d features\n3. Collapse check (feature STD + mean cosine similarity)\n4. kNN anomaly scoring (k=5, cosine distance)\n5. Threshold analysis + score distributions\n6. t-SNE embedding visualization\n7. Nearest neighbor retrieval (qualitative)\n8. Save checkpoints + zip for download","metadata":{}},{"id":"d9cdff35","cell_type":"code","source":"import os\nimport math\nimport time\nimport gc\nimport numpy as np\nimport random\nimport matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n\nimport torch\nimport torch.nn as nn\nimport torch.nn.functional as F\nfrom torch.utils.data import Dataset, DataLoader\n\nfrom torchvision.models import resnet18\n\nfrom tqdm import tqdm\nfrom sklearn.neighbors import NearestNeighbors\nfrom sklearn.manifold import TSNE\n\n# ── Reproducibility ──\nSEED = 42\nrandom.seed(SEED)\nnp.random.seed(SEED)\ntorch.manual_seed(SEED)\ntorch.cuda.manual_seed_all(SEED)\n\ndevice = \"cuda\" if torch.cuda.is_available() else \"cpu\"\nprint(\"Device:\", device)\nif device == \"cuda\":\n    print(torch.cuda.get_device_name(0))\n    print(f\"Memory: {torch.cuda.get_device_properties(0).total_memory / 1e9:.1f} GB\")","metadata":{},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"id":"730ac244","cell_type":"markdown","source":"## Hyperparameters\n\nTuned for better feature diversity and anomaly detection:\n- **Temperature 0.5** — with only 64 real negatives per step, low τ makes the task trivially easy → collapse. Higher τ forces the model to produce more discriminative features.\n- **LR 1e-3** — AdamW with cosine decay. Stronger than 3e-4 to escape partial-collapse basins.\n- **Projection dim 2048** — larger projection head (SimCLR v2) gives the encoder more room to learn.","metadata":{}},{"id":"be8994ae","cell_type":"code","source":"# ══════════════════════════════════════════════\n# Hyperparameters (shared across all 3 models)\n# ══════════════════════════════════════════════\nBATCH_SIZE     = 64\nGRAD_ACCUM     = 4            # effective batch = 64 × 4 = 256\nEPOCHS         = 20\nBASE_LR        = 1e-3         # stronger than 3e-4 to avoid collapse\nWARMUP_EPOCHS  = 3\nTEMPERATURE    = 0.5          # key fix: was 0.07 → caused near-collapse\nWEIGHT_DECAY   = 1e-4\nK_NEIGHBORS    = 5\nNUM_WORKERS    = 4\nIMG_SIZE       = 192\nPROJ_DIM       = 128          # projection output dimension\nPROJ_HIDDEN    = 2048         # projection hidden dimension (SimCLR v2)\n\nprint(f\"Effective batch size: {BATCH_SIZE * GRAD_ACCUM}\")\nprint(f\"Real negatives per step: {2 * BATCH_SIZE - 2}\")\nprint(f\"Estimated time per model: ~{EPOCHS * 11 / 60:.1f} hours\")","metadata":{},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"id":"2cd04309","cell_type":"markdown","source":"## Data Pipeline\n\n### Augmentation Strategy for Anomaly Detection (Clean Data Only)\n\nSince we **only have healthy, artifact-free images**, the augmentation design is critical:\n\n**Goal**: Teach the model what **normal variation** looks like → at test time, anything outside this distribution (artifacts) gets flagged.\n\n**Key principle**: We simulate **realistic scanner/anatomy variation** but intentionally do NOT simulate artifacts (motion ghosting, ringing, Gibbs, k-space spikes). Those must remain out-of-distribution.\n\n| Transform | Purpose | Probability |\n|-----------|---------|:-----------:|\n| **Elastic deformation** | Inter-subject anatomical variation | 30% |\n| **Affine (rot ±20°, scale 0.7–1.0)** | Patient positioning differences | 100% |\n| **Random crop** | Field-of-view variation | 100% |\n| **Horizontal flip** | Bilateral symmetry | 50% |\n| **Bias field** | B1 inhomogeneity (normal MRI physics) | 30% |\n| **Gamma correction** | Scanner intensity non-linearity | 40% |\n| **Intensity scale + shift** | Scanner gain/offset variation | 60% |\n| **Gaussian blur** | Partial volume / defocus | 30% |\n| **Sharpening** | Tissue edge contrast variation | 20% |\n| **Gaussian noise** | Thermal noise / acquisition noise | 30% |\n| **Random cutout** | Forces global context (detects local artifacts) | 30% |\n\n### Dataset Classes\n- `MRISimCLRDataset` — two augmented views for contrastive training\n- `MRICleanDataset` — unaugmented for deterministic feature extraction","metadata":{}},{"id":"c5d6056b","cell_type":"code","source":"# ══════════════════════════════════════════════\n# Augmentations — optimized for anomaly detection on CLEAN data\n# ══════════════════════════════════════════════\n# Strategy: we ONLY have healthy, artifact-free images. The augmentations\n# teach the model what \"normal variation\" looks like. At test time, anything\n# outside this learned distribution (artifacts) gets a high anomaly score.\n#\n# We simulate realistic MRI variations:\n#   - Scanner differences (gamma, bias field, intensity scaling)\n#   - Patient positioning (crop, flip, rotation, translation)\n#   - Acquisition noise (Gaussian noise, blur)\n#   - Anatomical variation (elastic deformation)\n#   - Partial visibility (cutout — forces global context)\n#\n# We intentionally do NOT simulate artifacts (motion ghosting, ringing,\n# k-space spikes) — those must remain out-of-distribution.\n\nimport scipy.ndimage\n\n\nclass SimCLRAugmentMRI:\n    \"\"\"Strong MRI-safe augmentations for contrastive anomaly detection.\n    All transforms simulate NORMAL scanner/anatomy variation only.\"\"\"\n\n    def __init__(self, img_size=192):\n        self.img_size = img_size\n\n    def _apply_once(self, img_np):\n        \"\"\"Apply augmentation pipeline to a single numpy image (H, W) float32 [0,1].\"\"\"\n        img = img_np.copy()\n        h, w = img.shape\n\n        # 1. Elastic deformation (p=0.3) — inter-subject anatomical variation\n        if random.random() < 0.3:\n            img = self._elastic_deform(img, alpha=15.0, sigma=4.0)\n\n        # 2. Random affine: rotation ±20° + scale 0.7–1.0 + translation ±5%\n        angle = random.uniform(-20, 20)\n        scale = random.uniform(0.7, 1.0)\n        tx = random.uniform(-0.05, 0.05) * w\n        ty = random.uniform(-0.05, 0.05) * h\n        img = self._affine_transform(img, angle, scale, tx, ty)\n\n        # 3. Random crop to target size\n        img = self._random_crop(img, self.img_size)\n\n        # 4. Horizontal flip (p=0.5)\n        if random.random() < 0.5:\n            img = np.flip(img, axis=1).copy()\n\n        # 5. Bias field simulation (p=0.3) — smooth B1 inhomogeneity (normal in MRI)\n        if random.random() < 0.3:\n            img = self._simulate_bias_field(img)\n\n        # 6. Gamma correction (p=0.4) — scanner intensity non-linearity\n        if random.random() < 0.4:\n            gamma = random.uniform(0.7, 1.5)\n            img = np.clip(img, 0, 1)\n            img = np.power(img, gamma)\n\n        # 7. Intensity scaling + shift (p=0.6) — scanner gain variation\n        if random.random() < 0.6:\n            gain = random.uniform(0.75, 1.25)\n            bias = random.uniform(-0.1, 0.1)\n            img = img * gain + bias\n\n        # 8. Gaussian blur (p=0.3) — slight defocus / partial volume effect\n        if random.random() < 0.3:\n            sigma = random.uniform(0.5, 2.0)\n            img = scipy.ndimage.gaussian_filter(img, sigma=sigma)\n\n        # 9. Sharpening (p=0.2) — varies tissue edge contrast\n        if random.random() < 0.2:\n            blurred = scipy.ndimage.gaussian_filter(img, sigma=1.0)\n            img = img + 0.5 * (img - blurred)\n\n        # 10. Gaussian noise (p=0.3) — thermal/acquisition noise\n        if random.random() < 0.3:\n            noise_std = random.uniform(0.01, 0.04)\n            img = img + noise_std * np.random.randn(*img.shape).astype(np.float32)\n\n        # 11. Random cutout (p=0.3) — forces global context learning\n        #     (helps detect local artifacts at test time)\n        if random.random() < 0.3:\n            img = self._random_cutout(img, max_ratio=0.2)\n\n        # Final clamp to valid range\n        img = np.clip(img, 0.0, 1.0).astype(np.float32)\n        return torch.from_numpy(img).unsqueeze(0)  # (1, H, W)\n\n    def __call__(self, x):\n        \"\"\"Returns two independently augmented views.\"\"\"\n        return self._apply_once(x), self._apply_once(x)\n\n    @staticmethod\n    def _elastic_deform(img, alpha=15.0, sigma=4.0):\n        \"\"\"Smooth elastic deformation — simulates anatomical variation.\"\"\"\n        shape = img.shape\n        dx = scipy.ndimage.gaussian_filter(np.random.randn(*shape), sigma) * alpha\n        dy = scipy.ndimage.gaussian_filter(np.random.randn(*shape), sigma) * alpha\n        y, x = np.meshgrid(np.arange(shape[0]), np.arange(shape[1]), indexing='ij')\n        coords = [np.clip(y + dy, 0, shape[0] - 1), np.clip(x + dx, 0, shape[1] - 1)]\n        return scipy.ndimage.map_coordinates(img, coords, order=1, mode='reflect').astype(np.float32)\n\n    @staticmethod\n    def _affine_transform(img, angle, scale, tx, ty):\n        \"\"\"Rotation + scale + translation via scipy.\"\"\"\n        h, w = img.shape\n        cos_a = math.cos(math.radians(angle)) * scale\n        sin_a = math.sin(math.radians(angle)) * scale\n        cx, cy = w / 2, h / 2\n        # Inverse affine for scipy\n        matrix = np.array([[cos_a, sin_a], [-sin_a, cos_a]]) / (scale * scale)\n        offset = np.array([cy - cos_a * cy - sin_a * cx + ty,\n                           cx + sin_a * cy - cos_a * cx + tx])\n        return scipy.ndimage.affine_transform(img, matrix, offset=offset,\n                                               order=1, mode='reflect').astype(np.float32)\n\n    @staticmethod\n    def _random_crop(img, target_size):\n        \"\"\"Random crop to target_size with reflect padding if needed.\"\"\"\n        h, w = img.shape\n        if h < target_size or w < target_size:\n            pad_h = max(0, target_size - h)\n            pad_w = max(0, target_size - w)\n            img = np.pad(img, ((0, pad_h), (0, pad_w)), mode='reflect')\n            h, w = img.shape\n        y = random.randint(0, h - target_size)\n        x = random.randint(0, w - target_size)\n        return img[y:y + target_size, x:x + target_size]\n\n    @staticmethod\n    def _simulate_bias_field(img):\n        \"\"\"Simulate smooth B1 bias field (normal MRI scanner inhomogeneity).\"\"\"\n        h, w = img.shape\n        x = np.linspace(-1, 1, w)\n        y = np.linspace(-1, 1, h)\n        xv, yv = np.meshgrid(x, y)\n        # Random low-order polynomial coefficients\n        a = random.uniform(-0.3, 0.3)\n        b = random.uniform(-0.3, 0.3)\n        c = random.uniform(-0.1, 0.1)\n        bias = 1.0 + a * xv + b * yv + c * (xv**2 + yv**2)\n        return (img * bias).astype(np.float32)\n\n    @staticmethod\n    def _random_cutout(img, max_ratio=0.2):\n        \"\"\"Zero out a random rectangular region.\"\"\"\n        h, w = img.shape\n        ch = int(h * random.uniform(0.05, max_ratio))\n        cw = int(w * random.uniform(0.05, max_ratio))\n        y = random.randint(0, h - ch)\n        x = random.randint(0, w - cw)\n        img = img.copy()\n        img[y:y + ch, x:x + cw] = 0.0\n        return img\n\n\nclass CleanTransform:\n    \"\"\"No augmentation — just convert to tensor.\"\"\"\n    def __call__(self, x):\n        return torch.from_numpy(x).unsqueeze(0).float()\n\n\n# ══════════════════════════════════════════════\n# Dataset classes\n# ══════════════════════════════════════════════\ndef find_npy_files(root_dir):\n    \"\"\"Recursively find all .npy files. Returns (paths, label_strings).\"\"\"\n    paths, labels = [], []\n    for dirpath, _, filenames in os.walk(root_dir):\n        npy_files = sorted([f for f in filenames if f.endswith(\".npy\")])\n        if npy_files:\n            folder_name = os.path.basename(dirpath)\n            for f in npy_files:\n                paths.append(os.path.join(dirpath, f))\n                labels.append(folder_name)\n    return paths, labels\n\n\nclass MRISimCLRDataset(Dataset):\n    \"\"\"Returns two augmented views (x1, x2) + label for contrastive training.\"\"\"\n    def __init__(self, root_dir, transform, name=\"\"):\n        self.transform = transform\n        self.paths, label_strs = find_npy_files(root_dir)\n        unique_labels = sorted(set(label_strs))\n        self.label_map = {n: i for i, n in enumerate(unique_labels)}\n        self.labels = [self.label_map[s] for s in label_strs]\n        print(f\"  [{name}] Loaded {len(self.paths)} slices | Labels: {self.label_map}\")\n\n    def __len__(self):\n        return len(self.paths)\n\n    def __getitem__(self, idx):\n        img = np.load(self.paths[idx]).astype(np.float32)\n        x1, x2 = self.transform(img)\n        return x1, x2, self.labels[idx]\n\n\nclass MRICleanDataset(Dataset):\n    \"\"\"Returns clean unaugmented images + labels for feature extraction.\"\"\"\n    def __init__(self, root_dir, transform=None, name=\"\"):\n        self.transform = transform or CleanTransform()\n        self.paths, label_strs = find_npy_files(root_dir)\n        unique_labels = sorted(set(label_strs))\n        self.label_map = {n: i for i, n in enumerate(unique_labels)}\n        self.labels = [self.label_map[s] for s in label_strs]\n\n    def __len__(self):\n        return len(self.paths)\n\n    def __getitem__(self, idx):\n        img = np.load(self.paths[idx]).astype(np.float32)\n        return self.transform(img), self.labels[idx]","metadata":{},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"id":"47be6d54","cell_type":"markdown","source":"## Model Architecture\n\n### Encoder: ResNet-18 (modified)\n- 1-channel input (conv1: 3×3, stride 1)\n- No maxpool (preserves spatial resolution for 192×192)\n- Output: 512-d after global average pooling\n\n### Projection Head (SimCLR v2 style)\n- 3-layer MLP: 512 → 2048 (BN+ReLU) → 2048 (BN+ReLU) → 128\n- Larger hidden dim prevents information bottleneck\n- Discarded after training\n\n### NT-Xent Loss\n- Temperature τ = 0.5 (tuned for small batch)\n- Forced fp32 computation (prevents overflow)","metadata":{}},{"id":"6af1685b","cell_type":"code","source":"# ══════════════════════════════════════════════\n# Model Definition\n# ══════════════════════════════════════════════\nclass Encoder(nn.Module):\n    def __init__(self):\n        super().__init__()\n        backbone = resnet18(weights=None)\n        backbone.conv1 = nn.Conv2d(1, 64, kernel_size=3, stride=1, padding=1, bias=False)\n        backbone.maxpool = nn.Identity()\n        self.features = nn.Sequential(\n            backbone.conv1, backbone.bn1, backbone.relu, backbone.maxpool,\n            backbone.layer1, backbone.layer2, backbone.layer3, backbone.layer4,\n            backbone.avgpool,\n        )\n\n    def forward(self, x):\n        return self.features(x).flatten(1)  # (B, 512)\n\n\nclass ProjectionHead(nn.Module):\n    \"\"\"3-layer projection head (SimCLR v2 style).\"\"\"\n    def __init__(self, in_dim=512, hidden_dim=2048, out_dim=128):\n        super().__init__()\n        self.net = nn.Sequential(\n            nn.Linear(in_dim, hidden_dim),\n            nn.BatchNorm1d(hidden_dim),\n            nn.ReLU(inplace=True),\n            nn.Linear(hidden_dim, hidden_dim),\n            nn.BatchNorm1d(hidden_dim),\n            nn.ReLU(inplace=True),\n            nn.Linear(hidden_dim, out_dim),\n        )\n\n    def forward(self, x):\n        return self.net(x)\n\n\nclass NTXentLoss(nn.Module):\n    def __init__(self, temperature=0.5):\n        super().__init__()\n        self.temperature = temperature\n\n    @torch.amp.autocast(\"cuda\", enabled=False)\n    def forward(self, z1, z2):\n        z1 = F.normalize(z1.float(), dim=1)\n        z2 = F.normalize(z2.float(), dim=1)\n\n        N = z1.size(0)\n        z = torch.cat([z1, z2], dim=0)\n        sim = torch.mm(z, z.T) / self.temperature\n\n        mask = torch.eye(2 * N, dtype=torch.bool, device=z.device)\n        sim.masked_fill_(mask, float(\"-inf\"))\n\n        positives = torch.cat([torch.diag(sim, N), torch.diag(sim, -N)])\n        loss = -positives + torch.logsumexp(sim, dim=1)\n        return loss.mean()","metadata":{},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"id":"59784670","cell_type":"markdown","source":"## Training & Evaluation Infrastructure\n\nReusable functions for all three training runs:\n- `train_epoch()` — forward + backward with gradient accumulation & clipping\n- `eval_epoch()` — validation loss (no grad)\n- `extract_features()` — L2-normalized encoder features from clean data\n- `run_full_analysis()` — complete evaluation pipeline (collapse check, kNN, t-SNE, plots)\n- `train_simclr()` — full training loop with checkpointing\n- `clear_gpu()` — free all GPU memory between runs","metadata":{}},{"id":"f362dd59","cell_type":"code","source":"# ══════════════════════════════════════════════\n# Training Infrastructure\n# ══════════════════════════════════════════════\nMAX_GRAD_NORM = 1.0\n\n\ndef clear_gpu():\n    \"\"\"Clear GPU memory between training runs.\"\"\"\n    gc.collect()\n    if torch.cuda.is_available():\n        torch.cuda.empty_cache()\n        torch.cuda.reset_peak_memory_stats()\n    print(f\"GPU memory cleared. Allocated: {torch.cuda.memory_allocated()/1e9:.2f} GB\")\n\n\ndef train_epoch(encoder, projector, loader, criterion, optimizer, scaler):\n    encoder.train()\n    projector.train()\n    total_loss = 0.0\n    optimizer.zero_grad()\n\n    for step, (x1, x2, _) in enumerate(loader):\n        x1, x2 = x1.to(device), x2.to(device)\n\n        with torch.amp.autocast(\"cuda\", enabled=(device == \"cuda\")):\n            z1 = projector(encoder(x1))\n            z2 = projector(encoder(x2))\n            loss = criterion(z1, z2) / GRAD_ACCUM\n\n        scaler.scale(loss).backward()\n\n        if (step + 1) % GRAD_ACCUM == 0 or (step + 1) == len(loader):\n            scaler.unscale_(optimizer)\n            torch.nn.utils.clip_grad_norm_(\n                list(encoder.parameters()) + list(projector.parameters()),\n                MAX_GRAD_NORM,\n            )\n            scaler.step(optimizer)\n            scaler.update()\n            optimizer.zero_grad()\n\n        total_loss += loss.item() * GRAD_ACCUM\n\n    return total_loss / len(loader)\n\n\n@torch.no_grad()\ndef eval_epoch(encoder, projector, loader, criterion):\n    encoder.eval()\n    projector.eval()\n    total_loss = 0.0\n\n    for x1, x2, _ in loader:\n        x1, x2 = x1.to(device), x2.to(device)\n        with torch.amp.autocast(\"cuda\", enabled=(device == \"cuda\")):\n            z1 = projector(encoder(x1))\n            z2 = projector(encoder(x2))\n            loss = criterion(z1, z2)\n        total_loss += loss.item()\n\n    return total_loss / len(loader)\n\n\n@torch.no_grad()\ndef extract_features(encoder, loader):\n    \"\"\"Extract L2-normalized encoder features.\"\"\"\n    encoder.eval()\n    feats, labels = [], []\n    for x, y in tqdm(loader, desc=\"Extracting\"):\n        x = x.to(device)\n        f = F.normalize(encoder(x), dim=1)\n        feats.append(f.cpu().numpy())\n        labels.append(y.numpy())\n    return np.concatenate(feats), np.concatenate(labels)","metadata":{},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"id":"e43a1445","cell_type":"code","source":"# ══════════════════════════════════════════════\n# Full Training Loop\n# ══════════════════════════════════════════════\ndef train_simclr(train_loader, val_loader, save_dir, model_name=\"SimCLR\"):\n    \"\"\"Train SimCLR and return (encoder, history).\"\"\"\n    os.makedirs(save_dir, exist_ok=True)\n    print(f\"\\n{'='*60}\")\n    print(f\"  Training: {model_name}\")\n    print(f\"  Save dir: {save_dir}\")\n    print(f\"  Train batches: {len(train_loader)} | Val batches: {len(val_loader)}\")\n    print(f\"{'='*60}\\n\")\n\n    encoder = Encoder().to(device)\n    projector = ProjectionHead(512, PROJ_HIDDEN, PROJ_DIM).to(device)\n\n    optimizer = torch.optim.AdamW(\n        list(encoder.parameters()) + list(projector.parameters()),\n        lr=BASE_LR, weight_decay=WEIGHT_DECAY,\n    )\n\n    def lr_lambda(epoch):\n        if epoch < WARMUP_EPOCHS:\n            return (epoch + 1) / WARMUP_EPOCHS\n        progress = (epoch - WARMUP_EPOCHS) / max(EPOCHS - WARMUP_EPOCHS, 1)\n        return 0.5 * (1.0 + math.cos(math.pi * progress))\n\n    scheduler = torch.optim.lr_scheduler.LambdaLR(optimizer, lr_lambda)\n    criterion = NTXentLoss(temperature=TEMPERATURE)\n    scaler = torch.amp.GradScaler(\"cuda\", enabled=(device == \"cuda\"))\n\n    history = {\"train_loss\": [], \"val_loss\": [], \"lr\": [], \"epoch_time\": []}\n    best_val_loss = float(\"inf\")\n    total_start = time.time()\n\n    for epoch in range(EPOCHS):\n        epoch_start = time.time()\n\n        t_loss = train_epoch(encoder, projector, train_loader, criterion, optimizer, scaler)\n        v_loss = eval_epoch(encoder, projector, val_loader, criterion)\n        scheduler.step()\n\n        epoch_time = time.time() - epoch_start\n        lr_now = scheduler.get_last_lr()[0]\n        history[\"train_loss\"].append(t_loss)\n        history[\"val_loss\"].append(v_loss)\n        history[\"lr\"].append(lr_now)\n        history[\"epoch_time\"].append(epoch_time)\n\n        elapsed = time.time() - total_start\n        eta = epoch_time * (EPOCHS - epoch - 1)\n\n        print(f\"Epoch {epoch+1}/{EPOCHS}  |  train={t_loss:.4f}  val={v_loss:.4f}  \"\n              f\"lr={lr_now:.6f}  |  {epoch_time:.0f}s  elapsed={elapsed/60:.1f}min  ETA={eta/60:.1f}min\")\n\n        if v_loss < best_val_loss:\n            best_val_loss = v_loss\n            torch.save({\n                \"epoch\": epoch + 1,\n                \"encoder\": encoder.state_dict(),\n                \"projector\": projector.state_dict(),\n                \"optimizer\": optimizer.state_dict(),\n                \"val_loss\": v_loss,\n            }, os.path.join(save_dir, \"best.pt\"))\n            print(f\"  ↑ Best model saved (val_loss={v_loss:.4f})\")\n\n        if (epoch + 1) % 5 == 0:\n            torch.save({\n                \"epoch\": epoch + 1,\n                \"encoder\": encoder.state_dict(),\n                \"projector\": projector.state_dict(),\n            }, os.path.join(save_dir, f\"epoch_{epoch+1}.pt\"))\n\n    # Save final\n    total_time = time.time() - total_start\n    torch.save({\n        \"epoch\": EPOCHS,\n        \"encoder\": encoder.state_dict(),\n        \"projector\": projector.state_dict(),\n        \"history\": history,\n    }, os.path.join(save_dir, \"final.pt\"))\n\n    print(f\"\\n✓ Training complete in {total_time/60:.1f} min ({total_time/3600:.2f} h)\")\n    print(f\"  Best val loss: {best_val_loss:.4f}\")\n    print(f\"  Avg epoch time: {np.mean(history['epoch_time']):.1f}s\")\n\n    # Load best encoder\n    best_ckpt = torch.load(os.path.join(save_dir, \"best.pt\"), map_location=device)\n    encoder.load_state_dict(best_ckpt[\"encoder\"])\n\n    return encoder, projector, history","metadata":{},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"id":"4793794c","cell_type":"code","source":"# ══════════════════════════════════════════════\n# Full Analysis Pipeline\n# ══════════════════════════════════════════════\ndef run_full_analysis(encoder, train_clean_loader, val_clean_loader,\n                      train_clean_dataset, val_clean_dataset, history, save_dir, model_name):\n    \"\"\"Run complete evaluation: features, collapse check, kNN, t-SNE, plots.\"\"\"\n    print(f\"\\n{'='*60}\")\n    print(f\"  Analysis: {model_name}\")\n    print(f\"{'='*60}\")\n\n    # ── 1. Training Curves ──\n    fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 3, figsize=(18, 5))\n    fig.suptitle(f\"{model_name} — Training Curves\", fontsize=14, y=1.02)\n\n    axes[0].plot(history[\"train_loss\"], label=\"Train\", linewidth=2)\n    axes[0].plot(history[\"val_loss\"], label=\"Val\", linewidth=2)\n    axes[0].set_xlabel(\"Epoch\"); axes[0].set_ylabel(\"NT-Xent Loss\")\n    axes[0].set_title(\"Loss Curves\"); axes[0].legend(); axes[0].grid(True, alpha=0.3)\n\n    axes[1].plot(history[\"lr\"], linewidth=2, color=\"green\")\n    axes[1].set_xlabel(\"Epoch\"); axes[1].set_ylabel(\"LR\")\n    axes[1].set_title(\"Learning Rate\"); axes[1].grid(True, alpha=0.3)\n\n    gap = [v - t for t, v in zip(history[\"train_loss\"], history[\"val_loss\"])]\n    axes[2].plot(gap, linewidth=2, color=\"red\")\n    axes[2].axhline(0, color=\"gray\", ls=\"--\", alpha=0.5)\n    axes[2].set_xlabel(\"Epoch\"); axes[2].set_ylabel(\"Val - Train\")\n    axes[2].set_title(\"Generalization Gap\"); axes[2].grid(True, alpha=0.3)\n\n    fig.tight_layout()\n    fig.savefig(os.path.join(save_dir, \"training_curves.png\"), dpi=150, bbox_inches=\"tight\")\n    plt.show()\n\n    # ── 2. Feature Extraction ──\n    print(\"\\nExtracting features...\")\n    train_feats, train_labels = extract_features(encoder, train_clean_loader)\n    val_feats, val_labels = extract_features(encoder, val_clean_loader)\n    print(f\"  Train: {train_feats.shape}, Val: {val_feats.shape}\")\n\n    # ── 3. Collapse Check ──\n    print(\"\\n── Collapse Check ──\")\n    n_check = min(2000, len(train_feats))\n    for name, feats in [(\"Train\", train_feats[:n_check]), (\"Val\", val_feats[:n_check])]:\n        std = np.std(feats, axis=0).mean()\n        sim_mat = np.dot(feats, feats.T)\n        off_diag = sim_mat[np.triu_indices_from(sim_mat, k=1)]\n        mean_sim = off_diag.mean()\n        status_std = \"✅\" if std > 0.01 else \"⚠️ COLLAPSE\"\n        status_sim = \"✅\" if mean_sim < 0.9 else \"⚠️ HIGH\"\n        print(f\"  {name}: STD={std:.4f} {status_std} | Mean cos sim={mean_sim:.4f} {status_sim}\")\n\n    # ── 4. kNN Anomaly Scoring ──\n    print(\"\\n── kNN Anomaly Scoring ──\")\n    nn_model = NearestNeighbors(n_neighbors=K_NEIGHBORS, metric=\"cosine\")\n    nn_model.fit(train_feats)\n    train_distances, _ = nn_model.kneighbors(train_feats)\n    val_distances, _ = nn_model.kneighbors(val_feats)\n    train_scores = train_distances.mean(axis=1)\n    val_scores = val_distances.mean(axis=1)\n\n    print(f\"  Train scores — mean: {train_scores.mean():.4f}, std: {train_scores.std():.4f}\")\n    print(f\"  Val scores   — mean: {val_scores.mean():.4f}, std: {val_scores.std():.4f}\")\n\n    # Score distributions\n    fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(14, 5))\n    fig.suptitle(f\"{model_name} — Anomaly Score Distributions\", fontsize=14, y=1.02)\n    axes[0].hist(train_scores, bins=60, alpha=0.7, color=\"steelblue\", edgecolor=\"white\")\n    axes[0].set_title(\"Train Scores\"); axes[0].set_xlabel(\"kNN Distance\")\n    axes[1].hist(val_scores, bins=60, alpha=0.7, color=\"coral\", edgecolor=\"white\")\n    axes[1].set_title(\"Val Scores\"); axes[1].set_xlabel(\"kNN Distance\")\n    fig.tight_layout()\n    fig.savefig(os.path.join(save_dir, \"anomaly_scores.png\"), dpi=150, bbox_inches=\"tight\")\n    plt.show()\n\n    # ── 5. Threshold Analysis ──\n    print(\"\\n── Threshold Analysis ──\")\n    for pct in [90, 95, 97.5, 99]:\n        thresh = np.percentile(train_scores, pct)\n        val_flagged = (val_scores > thresh).sum()\n        print(f\"  p{pct}: thresh={thresh:.4f} → {val_flagged}/{len(val_scores)} val flagged \"\n              f\"({100*val_flagged/len(val_scores):.1f}%)\")\n\n    # ── 6. t-SNE ──\n    print(\"\\nComputing t-SNE...\")\n    N_TSNE = min(3000, len(val_feats))\n    tsne = TSNE(n_components=2, perplexity=30, random_state=SEED, n_iter=1000)\n    emb = tsne.fit_transform(val_feats[:N_TSNE])\n    labels_sub = val_labels[:N_TSNE]\n    scores_sub = val_scores[:N_TSNE]\n\n    fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 3, figsize=(20, 6))\n    fig.suptitle(f\"{model_name} — t-SNE Embeddings\", fontsize=14, y=1.02)\n\n    axes[0].scatter(emb[:, 0], emb[:, 1], s=3, alpha=0.5, c=\"steelblue\")\n    axes[0].set_title(\"Unsupervised\"); axes[0].set_xticks([]); axes[0].set_yticks([])\n\n    sc = axes[1].scatter(emb[:, 0], emb[:, 1], s=3, alpha=0.5, c=labels_sub, cmap=\"coolwarm\")\n    axes[1].set_title(\"By Label\"); axes[1].set_xticks([]); axes[1].set_yticks([])\n    plt.colorbar(sc, ax=axes[1], shrink=0.8)\n\n    sc2 = axes[2].scatter(emb[:, 0], emb[:, 1], s=3, alpha=0.5, c=scores_sub, cmap=\"YlOrRd\")\n    axes[2].set_title(\"Anomaly Score\"); axes[2].set_xticks([]); axes[2].set_yticks([])\n    plt.colorbar(sc2, ax=axes[2], shrink=0.8)\n\n    fig.tight_layout()\n    fig.savefig(os.path.join(save_dir, \"tsne.png\"), dpi=150, bbox_inches=\"tight\")\n    plt.show()\n\n    # ── 7. Cosine Similarity Distribution ──\n    subset = torch.tensor(val_feats[:2000])\n    sim_matrix = torch.mm(subset, subset.T).numpy()\n    upper_tri = sim_matrix[np.triu_indices_from(sim_matrix, k=1)]\n\n    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 5))\n    ax.hist(upper_tri, bins=100, color=\"mediumpurple\", edgecolor=\"white\", alpha=0.8)\n    ax.axvline(upper_tri.mean(), color=\"red\", ls=\"--\", label=f\"Mean: {upper_tri.mean():.3f}\")\n    ax.set_title(f\"{model_name} — Pairwise Cosine Similarity\")\n    ax.set_xlabel(\"Cosine Similarity\"); ax.legend()\n    fig.tight_layout()\n    fig.savefig(os.path.join(save_dir, \"similarity_dist.png\"), dpi=150, bbox_inches=\"tight\")\n    plt.show()\n\n    # ── 8. Nearest Neighbor Retrieval ──\n    nn_vis = NearestNeighbors(n_neighbors=6, metric=\"cosine\").fit(val_feats)\n    indices = random.sample(range(len(val_feats)), 3)\n\n    fig, axes = plt.subplots(3, 6, figsize=(15, 7.5))\n    fig.suptitle(f\"{model_name} — Nearest Neighbor Retrieval\", fontsize=14, y=1.02)\n    for row, q_idx in enumerate(indices):\n        _, nn_idxs = nn_vis.kneighbors([val_feats[q_idx]])\n        for col, idx in enumerate(nn_idxs[0]):\n            img = np.load(val_clean_dataset.paths[idx])\n            axes[row][col].imshow(img, cmap=\"gray\", vmin=0, vmax=1)\n            axes[row][col].axis(\"off\")\n            axes[row][col].set_title(\"Query\" if col == 0 else f\"NN-{col}\", fontsize=9)\n    fig.tight_layout()\n    fig.savefig(os.path.join(save_dir, \"nn_retrieval.png\"), dpi=150, bbox_inches=\"tight\")\n    plt.show()\n\n    # ── 9. Top Anomalies ──\n    top_k = 10\n    top_indices = np.argsort(val_scores)[-top_k:][::-1]\n\n    fig, axes = plt.subplots(2, 5, figsize=(15, 6))\n    fig.suptitle(f\"{model_name} — Top-10 Most Anomalous Slices\", fontsize=14)\n    for i, idx in enumerate(top_indices):\n        ax = axes[i // 5][i % 5]\n        img = np.load(val_clean_dataset.paths[idx])\n        ax.imshow(img, cmap=\"gray\", vmin=0, vmax=1)\n        ax.set_title(f\"Score: {val_scores[idx]:.4f}\", fontsize=9)\n        ax.axis(\"off\")\n    fig.tight_layout()\n    fig.savefig(os.path.join(save_dir, \"top_anomalies.png\"), dpi=150, bbox_inches=\"tight\")\n    plt.show()\n\n    # ── 10. Save scoring data ──\n    chosen_threshold = np.percentile(train_scores, 95)\n    np.savez(\n        os.path.join(save_dir, \"scoring.npz\"),\n        train_scores=train_scores, val_scores=val_scores,\n        train_feats=train_feats, val_feats=val_feats,\n        train_labels=train_labels, val_labels=val_labels,\n        threshold_p95=chosen_threshold,\n    )\n    print(f\"\\n✓ All results saved to {save_dir}/\")\n    print(f\"  Files: {os.listdir(save_dir)}\")\n\n    return train_feats, val_feats, train_scores, val_scores","metadata":{},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"id":"aed8c919","cell_type":"markdown","source":"## Data Discovery\n\nExplore the Kaggle dataset directories to find the correct paths.","metadata":{}},{"id":"6393152d","cell_type":"code","source":"# ══════════════════════════════════════════════\n# Discover dataset paths\n# ══════════════════════════════════════════════\nKNEE_ROOT = \"/kaggle/input/datasets/kaustubhratna/fast-mri-preprocessed-kaust\"\nBRAIN_ROOT = \"/kaggle/input/datasets/kaustubhratna/preprocessed-ixi-brain\"\n\ndef show_tree(path, prefix=\"\", max_depth=3, depth=0):\n    if depth >= max_depth:\n        return\n    try:\n        entries = sorted(os.listdir(path))\n    except (PermissionError, FileNotFoundError) as e:\n        print(f\"{prefix}⚠️ {e}\")\n        return\n    dirs = [e for e in entries if os.path.isdir(os.path.join(path, e))]\n    files = [e for e in entries if os.path.isfile(os.path.join(path, e))]\n    if files:\n        npy = [f for f in files if f.endswith('.npy')]\n        if npy:\n            print(f\"{prefix}📄 {len(npy)} .npy files (e.g., {npy[0]})\")\n        for f in [x for x in files if not x.endswith('.npy')][:3]:\n            print(f\"{prefix}📄 {f}\")\n    for d in dirs:\n        print(f\"{prefix}📁 {d}/\")\n        show_tree(os.path.join(path, d), prefix + \"    \", max_depth, depth + 1)\n\nprint(\"=\" * 50)\nprint(\"KNEE Dataset:\")\nprint(\"=\" * 50)\nshow_tree(KNEE_ROOT)\n\nprint(f\"\\n{'='*50}\")\nprint(\"BRAIN Dataset:\")\nprint(\"=\" * 50)\nshow_tree(BRAIN_ROOT)","metadata":{},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"id":"19026cfb","cell_type":"code","source":"# ══════════════════════════════════════════════\n# Configure dataset paths\n# ══════════════════════════════════════════════\n# ⚠️ UPDATE THESE based on the directory tree output above\nKNEE_TRAIN = os.path.join(KNEE_ROOT, \"train\")\nKNEE_VAL   = os.path.join(KNEE_ROOT, \"val\")\nBRAIN_TRAIN = os.path.join(BRAIN_ROOT, \"train\")\nBRAIN_VAL   = os.path.join(BRAIN_ROOT, \"val\")\n\n# Verify paths exist\nfor name, path in [(\"Knee train\", KNEE_TRAIN), (\"Knee val\", KNEE_VAL),\n                   (\"Brain train\", BRAIN_TRAIN), (\"Brain val\", BRAIN_VAL)]:\n    exists = os.path.exists(path)\n    count = len(find_npy_files(path)[0]) if exists else 0\n    status = \"✅\" if count > 0 else \"❌\"\n    print(f\"  {status} {name}: {path} ({count} files)\")","metadata":{},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"id":"5c0aa34f","cell_type":"markdown","source":"---\n# Part 1: Knee Only (FastMRI)\n\nTrain SimCLR on **knee MRI slices only**. Single anatomy, single contrast (KNEE subfolder).\n\nExpected characteristics:\n- Homogeneous anatomy → features should cluster tightly\n- ~14,000 train slices (442 volumes × ~32 slices)\n- Good anomaly detection on knee-specific artifacts","metadata":{}},{"id":"63c665a9","cell_type":"code","source":"# ══════════════════════════════════════════════\n# PART 1: KNEE — Data Loaders\n# ══════════════════════════════════════════════\nprint(\"Loading Knee datasets...\")\naug = SimCLRAugmentMRI(IMG_SIZE)\n\nknee_train_ds = MRISimCLRDataset(KNEE_TRAIN, aug, name=\"Knee-Train\")\nknee_val_ds   = MRISimCLRDataset(KNEE_VAL, aug, name=\"Knee-Val\")\n\nknee_train_loader = DataLoader(knee_train_ds, batch_size=BATCH_SIZE, shuffle=True,\n                               num_workers=NUM_WORKERS, pin_memory=True, drop_last=True)\nknee_val_loader = DataLoader(knee_val_ds, batch_size=BATCH_SIZE, shuffle=False,\n                             num_workers=NUM_WORKERS, pin_memory=True)\n\n# Clean loaders for feature extraction\nknee_train_clean = MRICleanDataset(KNEE_TRAIN, name=\"Knee-Train-Clean\")\nknee_val_clean   = MRICleanDataset(KNEE_VAL, name=\"Knee-Val-Clean\")\n\nknee_train_clean_loader = DataLoader(knee_train_clean, batch_size=BATCH_SIZE, shuffle=False,\n                                     num_workers=NUM_WORKERS, pin_memory=True)\nknee_val_clean_loader = DataLoader(knee_val_clean, batch_size=BATCH_SIZE, shuffle=False,\n                                   num_workers=NUM_WORKERS, pin_memory=True)\n\n# Preview sample\nsample = np.load(knee_train_ds.paths[0])\nprint(f\"\\nSample: shape={sample.shape}, range=[{sample.min():.3f}, {sample.max():.3f}]\")","metadata":{},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"id":"2e5daebb","cell_type":"code","source":"# ══════════════════════════════════════════════\n# PART 1: KNEE — Augmentation Preview\n# ══════════════════════════════════════════════\nfig, axes = plt.subplots(2, 5, figsize=(12.5, 5))\nfig.suptitle(\"Knee — Augmentation Preview\", fontsize=14, y=1.02)\n\nfor row in range(2):\n    idx = random.randint(0, len(knee_train_clean) - 1)\n    raw = np.load(knee_train_clean.paths[idx]).astype(np.float32)\n    axes[row][0].imshow(raw, cmap=\"gray\", vmin=0, vmax=1)\n    axes[row][0].set_title(\"Original\", fontweight=\"bold\", fontsize=9)\n    axes[row][0].axis(\"off\")\n    for col in range(1, 5):\n        v, _ = aug(raw)\n        axes[row][col].imshow(v[0], cmap=\"gray\", vmin=0, vmax=1)\n        axes[row][col].set_title(f\"View {col}\", fontsize=9)\n        axes[row][col].axis(\"off\")\n\nfig.tight_layout()\nplt.show()","metadata":{},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"id":"32bb5716","cell_type":"code","source":"# ══════════════════════════════════════════════\n# PART 1: KNEE — Train SimCLR\n# ══════════════════════════════════════════════\nKNEE_SAVE = \"/kaggle/working/checkpoints/simclr_knee\"\nknee_encoder, knee_projector, knee_history = train_simclr(\n    knee_train_loader, knee_val_loader, KNEE_SAVE, model_name=\"SimCLR-Knee\"\n)","metadata":{},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"id":"f7c02e02","cell_type":"code","source":"# ══════════════════════════════════════════════\n# PART 1: KNEE — Full Analysis\n# ══════════════════════════════════════════════\nknee_results = run_full_analysis(\n    knee_encoder, knee_train_clean_loader, knee_val_clean_loader,\n    knee_train_clean, knee_val_clean, knee_history, KNEE_SAVE, \"SimCLR-Knee\"\n)","metadata":{},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"id":"71478886","cell_type":"code","source":"# ══════════════════════════════════════════════\n# PART 1: KNEE — Cleanup GPU\n# ══════════════════════════════════════════════\ndel knee_encoder, knee_projector\ndel knee_train_loader, knee_val_loader\ndel knee_train_clean_loader, knee_val_clean_loader\nclear_gpu()","metadata":{},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"id":"ffcc891d","cell_type":"markdown","source":"---\n# Part 2: Brain Only (IXI)\n\nTrain SimCLR on **brain MRI slices** (T1 + T2 mixed). Single anatomy, mixed contrast.\n\nExpected characteristics:\n- Two scan types (T1/T2) with different contrast → model should learn anatomy-level features\n- ~25,600 train slices (400 volumes × 64 slices)\n- Bimodal feature structure (T1 cluster vs T2 cluster expected in t-SNE)","metadata":{}},{"id":"998e8e19","cell_type":"code","source":"# ══════════════════════════════════════════════\n# PART 2: BRAIN — Data Loaders\n# ══════════════════════════════════════════════\nprint(\"Loading Brain datasets...\")\naug = SimCLRAugmentMRI(IMG_SIZE)\n\nbrain_train_ds = MRISimCLRDataset(BRAIN_TRAIN, aug, name=\"Brain-Train\")\nbrain_val_ds   = MRISimCLRDataset(BRAIN_VAL, aug, name=\"Brain-Val\")\n\nbrain_train_loader = DataLoader(brain_train_ds, batch_size=BATCH_SIZE, shuffle=True,\n                                num_workers=NUM_WORKERS, pin_memory=True, drop_last=True)\nbrain_val_load